  <p>Use our <a href="/chinese/tools/pinyin-converter/">Pinyin Converter</a> to check the correct pinyin and tones for any text you are practicing, and review our <a href="/chinese/blog/chinese-tones-guide/">Complete Tones Guide</a> for detailed tone training methods.</p>

  <p>Tone practice is where many learners give up too early, but it is the single most important pronunciation skill in Mandarin. Native speakers rely on tones to distinguish meaning far more than English speakers rely on stress patterns. A practical daily exercise is to pick ten two-syllable words from your Anki deck and practice saying each one five times while exaggerating the tones. Record yourself on your phone, play it back, and compare with the audio in Pleco or Forvo. Over time, your muscle memory will internalize the correct pitch contours and tones will become automatic rather than something you have to consciously think about.</p>

